caption: So great I had to put a review on my blog
Nice food and great atmosphere.

Skip Miss Shirley’s and head here for shrimp and grits! Everything I ordered from here was DELICIOUS, I ate here twice on our trip and will dream of this food when I’m home. Friendly, joyful, courteous team!!!

It's not fast food. It's great food! If you're in a hurry take it to McDonald's. If you have time for a great meal cooked by great people with great personality, this is your place. Pig Towns pride right here y'all!!!! Don't sleep on Kim's creations! She's sweet and cooks with much love.

This is a hit or miss. The food has potential to be extreamly good or just Aiight. But I come anyways as I know I will never get bad food. Dont come unless you have time!!!!! This is not a knock on them as I have never had to wait outrageously long. But it is food that takes time to cook. Reasonable amount of time. They have a few things here and there to improve on. But I enjoy them as a nice lil food spot.
The food was unexpectedly amazing
Local business with excellent food. Sticky wings are a must.
Will just say the FOOD is great and the owner takes care of all her guests well.
Great cheeseburgers and fries
Jabril is great and so is the food. I had fried fish and sweet potato fries. Awesome!  Second time I went back, the owner who is a Lady was rude, and dismissive. I will NEVER go back there.
Those sticky wings are the bomb! Ordered the hamburger and it was perfect there was no need to add any condiments it was perfect in juicy how it was delivered. The wife lovef the turkey burger

I had so much about their Sticky Wings so I figured I'd try them out. The wings had good flavor, but they could've added a little more sauce. They were a little dry to me. The mac and cheese wasn't so great. There was barely any cheese and it was dry, also. I must say, the Awesome Fries were delish, though. I come back just for those and if I get the wings again,  I'll ask for extra sauce.
We had the sticky wings and fries. The food was great and the service was excellent. We will be back!

I ordered sticky wings with awesome fries. I picked the pulled chicken instead of pulled beef. The fries were soooooo good. Not what I need when I'm trying to lose weight. Lol The wings were cooked well. I loved the cilantro and green onions. They gave the food a different taste. I was expecting the sticky wings to have more flavor aside from the cilantro and green onions. It was still good. The apple bread pudding wasn't the best. It taste the best with apples, but the piece I had only seemed to have one apple. I gave 4 instead of 5 stars because they gave me a certain time frame to pick up my food. I got there a few minutes after that time and then had to wait another 15-20min because my food wasn't ready.
Delicious food and a very friendly atmosphere. The service is professional and the prices are fair.
Some if the best fried catfish I've ever had! The garlic fries were good too.
Awesome fries with BBQ pulled chicken so delicious!! The staff is nice and helpful. Be careful with parking avoid the 7-11 lot, you will get towed.
The owner was amazingly nice and shared other dishes that they offered to us as we waited for our amazing sticky wings. It is a super nice, Low key establishment with badass food.

Amazing atmosphere. Super comfortable vibe. Incredible food. Get the awesome fries and sticky wings. Absolutely killer. Bread pudding was divine. Our server Jabril was so sweet and friendly. And a wonderful singer. We’ll be back next time we’re in town.
Best intimate restaurant
Sticky wings, whew yummmmmm! Everything is good 👍🏽
Great food and a great spot to chill at.

Went there today have terrible service. I went in about 11:05am the server left and went to another store to get ice. On top of that I was the only guest in house, I ordered a chicken and wild rice soup which they were out of . Then I wings they took 45 mins and they had no blue cheese .   Then I ordered a burger for my entree at the same time I ordered my wings the burger took an hour and I’m still the only guest in house it was just all around bad today .

Food was delicious. Kids enjoyed it. The ultimate tasters. Short staffed, but he was extremely sweet. Crowd grew while there. Food took a few minutes, but it showed the love they produced. Not bad. Just no more Fridays.

Kim and Cat were extremely accommodating to my dietary restrictions at a privately catered event. Their food was not only delicious but was also presented with so much attention to detail. They are also amazingly wonderful and warm humans and I recommend working with them at any event!

Delicious food--burger was juicy, wings were flavorful, and the awesome fries were generously loaded with toppings, great for sharing. Nothing that we ordered was bad. Service was also very attentive and friendly. Would definitely recommend this as a great low-key spot.
OMG!!!  This is my favorite spot when visiting Baltimore!!!  My family really enjoyed ourselves and the service was outstanding!!!  THE WAITER, Jabril was GREAT!!!  #NCINTHEHOUSE
Great food ..BYOB

This place is absolutely amazing. You must try the Sticky Wings. The burgers were juicy and obviously handcrafted. Best grits in north or south and then they deep fry them into delicious little balls. Jabril took amazing care of us. Looks like any other coffee shop but is the best thoughtful execution of classic American. Will come back every time I’m in Baltimore.
Nice little cafe
Amazing wings! Amazing Business.Will stop back when we are in Baltimore!
The atmosphere was great the food was amazing the service was spectacular. I must go to. I absolutely plan on returning.
Place was good but lack of public parking lead to my car getting towed to the bad part of town
Sticky wings are great and food was generally very good, however, service was very slow although the staff was apologetic about it!

Wonderful down home cooking! Had the catfish and the Mac and cheese! So good!  You have to try the sticky wings too. The flavor has a warm spice but is nicely sweet and delish!  The service was also great and they made us feel like old friends on our first visit.

Perfect place in Pigtown! Young, black professional employees and chef! Garlic Parm fries, the famous sticky wings 14 count, and the soup of the day (Friday) was Turkey, kale, and potato soup. Perfect!
Love the story behind how this restaurant came to be and the food is just as amazing. I'll continue to go back every chance I get. This day I had the savory waffle with shrimp.

The atmosphere and service of break bread is a whole vibe. If I had time to dine in I definitely would have. The menu gives you just enough options and the staff is knowledgeable of the items. The actual food itself was AMAAAAZING!!! I can’t wait to come back.
Friendly service and great tasting food, what more could you ask for!!!
Sticky wings and burger were both delicious. The service was great, the staff is very friendly. I would definitely come back if I am in the area again

Wowsa! I wasn't all that hungry today but wanted a small lunch so I popped by this Pigtown institution and it was AMAZING! The vibe, decor, music, staff, food and unlimited refills on Diet Coke were just right. I was in heaven! Got the Chipotle Potato Salad. It was perfect. Prices were good too. Found parking right outside on the street and sat at the counter. Cozy as can be. It feels very welcoming and comfy. I will be back.
Wings are the best

We were back home and decided to head to Baltimore to spend the weekend with our friend. As we were walking we saw The Breaking Bread restaurant and decided to stop in. Thank GOD we did!! The food was absolutely amazing!! Fresh, made from scratch, down home cooking. The owners(husband and wife) were such great, friendly people.  The ambiance is very welcoming. We appreciate ALL the hospitality and love!!  See you guys soon!!
Qwners were very friendly. The food was delicious and service by Jabril was wonderful. Would definitely return again!
Good music accompanied by great customer service. Fantastic meal with good portions. Their sweet tea is a must have!
The food was excellent as well as the service. I can't wait to visit again for breakfast! One of the best restaurant meals I've had in quite some time.

Visited Breaking Bread for the first time. I enjoyed their delicious sticky wings and we had a yummy hamburger. The bread pudding was great as was the chocolate cake. I liked the vibe and hospitality of this restaurant
Excellent, Good Food
Taking back or should I say off my feet by the great creation of sticky wings. Friendly surrounding and great hosts. A must repeat.
The food was amazing. The waitress named Donna needs an attitude adjustment. Poor service. Moody.
Baltimore's best kept secret!!!!! The sticky wings and awesome fries are to die for!!!! Great service & atmosphere!!!
For my first experience it was not a good one. I had a one hr lunch break and in 30 mins I was not even asked for my order.  Maybe I will try again. It looks like a cool place nice vibe.
Freindly, cozy place where love is in control. From the owner to the waiter the service is impeccable. This is truly a treat.
A really cool spot that I absolutely have fallen in love with. Good people and great good. Their menu is a mix of classic and new. Try that jerked Burnie and their lemonade!
Delicious! Great Food! Great atmosphere! Get the sticky wings and jerk wings!
Love eatting local, and this place didn't disappoint! Jabril and Kimberly were amazing! Great food, better service! Will be making this a yearly stop!
I loved the staff! The food was amazing too. The whole feel of the restaurant was cookout at grandma's. It just felt comfortable and homey. Will definitely go back!
Great food and excellent service

The environment felt so homely. I walked in and I was treated as though I was part of the family. The server Jabriel was great person to talk to and he was extremely nice. I was hesitant about ordering the jerk lamb burger because of the spices but he assured me that it was good. And boy was he RIGHT! ( I was glad he was right) The burger was jam packed with flavors, juicy and delicious. It was so moist that it was practically coming out of my hand.  And the sweet potato fries I had with it was an excellent touch  not to greasy and not too sweet nor salty it was just right. I loved every minute of eating my meal and wished it last longer. Not to mention my server Jabriel also allowed me to sample the sticky wing! for FREE. The server really treats you like family and he is an all around nice guy.  The ambience and the experience of this place is A+++. It is a hidden gem that you do not want to miss.

I cannot imagine why anyone would give Breaking Bread anything but 5 stars! We had the Awesome fries. Name fits!  Food may take awhile because it is NOT frozen food dropped in a frier. If you have to wait a bit, chill. Food is worth the wait. Owners and staff are so nice, friendly. They told us empty plates were happy plates. Ours definitely were happy. This was our first time to visit. It will not be our last.  Kathy From Texas!!

The food is amazing but what I really love is that sexy waiter named Jabriel! Such a charismatic, charming, and personable person and he never leaves you unchecked; always coming to you and asking if you're okay and if the food was done and prepared in the way that you ordered. Truly, in all of my years of eating on this Earth, I have NEVER seen someone as spot-on and amazing as he is.  He made the food (which is already at 10 stars,) 10 times the more awesome. Thank you for hosting me and hopefully, this becomes a recurring thing!

Food was delicious. Lost a star b/c of initial Interaction. We weren't greeted, the restaurant was empty and two people of the three standing behind the bar looked at us and turned heading into the kitchen. So we stood at the bar and asked the 3rd gentleman on the phone, do we seat ourselves or wait... We decided to sit at bar. Besides the not so great first impression, everything else was good. Customer service was much better and we will be back.

I can’t say enough good things about this place! I walked in and was treated like an old friend or family. The owner came over and talked to me and is incredibly nice! Service was fast and attentive, food was great (try the jerk sandwich panini style!). Plus they had cool artwork upstairs! Truly a gem in Pigtown.

This place is awesome. Went when it wasn't too crowded. Service was awesome and everyone was very friendly. Burgers couldn't have been better and the garlic parmesan fries were bangin'. Couldn't recommend more
No BREAD! Really!
Great loving resturant with amazing food and friendly people. 💕💕 Highly Recommend !
Great experience and comfort food.

WOW -delicious, beautiful and perfectly prepared food - we loved the salmon salad (jerk seasoning), mushroom burger, mac & cheese, BREAD PUDDING, turkey kale soup, fries - everything!  We love this restaurant and looking forward to future visits!

Great place! Our server Jabril was the best: he was very attentive, he helped us with the menu, and he suggested his amazing sweet tea. The Awesome fries will pulled BBQ beef were amazing!!! Also the bartender and chef personally came out the check on us too. The whole restaurant was a vibe, especially the art. Definitely will be back before we head home.
I was surprised

Kim gives you the best vibe you could ever get.. She makes sure you feel welcome, & that this is the place you where meant to eat at.. The food is mind blowing.. Everything taste freshly made..  Burgers are a banger.. Garlic Parm french fries 😍.. & the wings, OMG! Nothing like supporting black owned businesses!

It’s a beautiful spring Saturday, my girlfriend and I came to Baltimore for some furnishing shopping and found this place on google maps with a 4.7 star review. We got here before 12pm and there was one table only with a couple drinking tea. We ordered right away after asking for water and coffee. When the coffee arrived I knew I was in for a “great time”. Rancid, cold, thick dark and biter coffee. I asked for cream, as you can see in the picture, but couldn’t do it more than a couple of sips. The waitress brought only one water and no stirrer to mix the coffee with the cream. Now, it’s 12:50 and we haven’t seen our food yet. Actually just came and the oil coming out of it it’s just insane. Food missed on every point, service very poor. Really needs some cleaning and dusting, can only imagine the kitchen...
1st visit. Food was very good. Catfish nuggets and wings! Sweet tea is good too.
Great Food, love the peacefulness...

I don't normally write reviews but i will for this restaurant. The food was amazing. The best wings I ever had and there sweet tea was perfect.  But the best part of my dining experience was the customer service. I felt like i was visiting my family and you can't get that from other restaurants.  1,000,000/10 stars.

It's highly unfortunate that it is so difficult to support a black owned business. My fiancé Tasia Talbert posted a honest review about getting sick from eating Breaking Bread's "sticky wings". This is not the first time we have eaten here. Previous orders were ok and non contaminated. The quick and unprofessional response from the owner has prompted me to call the health department to report this atrocity. The customer service here is less than stellar and should be added on the list of improvements needed.

Went in the word of a friend, I'm very particular about new spots, I had the jerk lamb and Turkey burger with garlic parmesan fries, it was unbelievably delicious, staff was friendly and courteous, polite would be an understatement, cant wait til I'm hungry again.
Owner personally greeted us.

VERY BAD!!!  they have limited drink options. One of their options were coke which was a 2 liter that was just chilling on the counter!! Opened and all like the server been sipping on it . also I witnessed the man cook food WITHOUT any gloves which encouraged me and my boyfriend to leave the restaurant. The owner needs to come back and get things in order .
The food was phenomenal I had the Mac & Cheese and sticky wings 😋 The staff was friendly and courteous, great vibe. Will definitely be returning

I'm so glad we found this place while visiting Baltimore. The staff was so friendly and helpful, it was more like eating at a friends house than a restaurant. They put kids songs on the TV when my family walked in, we played board games while they made our food and the food was excellent.  Everything seemed handmade and fresh, my 5 year old said it was better than McDonlds, which is the standard of all good food (for him, clearly). I had their famous sticky wings, which were crispy and sweet, made with  some kind of savory honey sauce with a little spice. I cant recommend this place highly enough!
The wings where awesome.and the people where every inviting
The restaurant was cold and very loud.  I was looking for something cozy where I could have a conversation and this wasn't the spot.
The wings are bomb! I can't wait to go back!
We loved our burgers and fries, and the bread pudding was one of the best desserts I have ever had.
Only been there once but I enjoyed the experience.

We ordered from Breaking Bread for a corporate event and the food was amazing! I emailed asking for suggestions and Kimberly gave me reasonable suggestions and a reasonable quote! Ed delivered and set up the food and made sure we had everything we needed. I definitely would recommend using the company for catering.

I finally made it out to Breaking Bread as I've been marked it on my "places to go" list. Glad I was able to! The Jerk/turkey lamb burger was very enjoyable. They also offer self proclaimed Famous Sticky Wings that I also tried. I was more impressed with the burger than the wings. Not saying they were bad, just average wings, nothing special. I'm willing to give them another shot at a later visit. I did take them to go as I finished my burger and didnt have room for the rest. The atmosphere is welcoming. Cool spot for a quick lunch. I will say, their Red Velvet cake looked wonderful. I was being the good husband and didnt partake, but WHEN you do please enjoy it for me.

There has to be something if you go to a restaurant 3 nights in a row in a 5-day vacation to Baltimore! The freshest wing I have ever had! Great music, incredible people! Do not miss this place and their wings!
Delicious food!
Good food and the friendliest staff ever.
Great place! Great food! Great owners and staff!
Fresh, made to order food ! Black Family owned ,super inviting dining area and did I say the food is DELICIOUS!
Great food but long line wait for food

I'm sold! This is my new favorite place in Baltimore. They treated my daughter and me like family. We practically had dinner with the owners right at the alcohol-free bar. We ate great, homemade food, talked about music, watched videos, laughed... My daughter and I love wings. So their award winning "Sticky Wings" plus the "Hot Honey" were a fun combination.
Pros: The food was inexpensive & good. Cons: I ordered 6 wings & fries. It took nearly 30 minutes to receive.

Incredible food, incredible atmosphere, incredibly kind and charming service. This place has so much character and is a gem. The service isn't always super fast but there's a lot of pride in their family-owned restaurant and in their food (did I mention the food is delicious?). If you don't drop by, you're missing out.
Great place to eat. The shrimps and grits are awesome
Awesome fries were great. The staff seemed to be polite and welcoming I'll definitely be back again
Wings always fabulous
Absolutely wonderful experience
Family who own the place beautiful friendly people. Love the atmosphere
The sticky wings are the absolute best. Our server Jabril was a delightful, and service-oriented young man.

OK place. A little pricey, but it's worth it once in a while. However, the gentleman who took my order was clearly intoxicated and didn't even get my order right. For $12 a burger, I expect you to be sober and comprehend what I am ordering.
I liked it and I will be back real cool spot
Best sticky wings
The most engaging owners of all time. Guests get treated as friends, authentically and not in a pushy way.
Great Food!!!!!!!!
Delicious soul food,  super friendly staff. Long wait because they make everything to order (sooo worth the wait) and they have fun games to play while you wait
Breaking bread is where great down home cooking meets down-to-earth people!  Come experience for yourself!
Amazing place to eat with awesome people in welcoming environment.

"Great food. Not fast food." That's what they tell you but I really want to emphasize that Kim's family owned and operated neighborhood restaurant is very much that: family operated. What it lacks in food Network style efficiency, it makes up for with the love and attention of a home cooked meal, served by a loving family member. If you need a quick bite before the game, get fast food. but if you have time, bring your friends and family, a bottle of wine, and spend some time with Kim and her family. Try the wings, turkey burger, Mac and cheese and the awesome fish basket.
Always an excellent atmosphere, great service and wonderful food.
Great food,  mission & service!!! One of my top faves for sure
Great place, eat here is like eating with family.

Fantastic experience today for lunch! Our friendly server brought homemade tortilla chips, and a sample of their award-winning sticky wings while we were waiting for our meal - so good! The Turkey Burger was amazing.  The Roast Beef & Cheddar Panini and the Bacon Cheeseburger were delicious. The chipotle potato salad was superb.  Oooooohhhhh, and the Chef’s homemade Cookies ‘n Cream Cheesecake ... divine!The best music videos were playing in the background - all-in-all this was a great choice for my husband and I to meet my son.  Kudos to the Chef, Tyree and the fabulous service by Jabril!‬ (I 💕 the playlist!)  Baltimore- if you haven’t already - you need to check out this friendly, eclectic and very “chill” restaurant soon!

This restaurant has the feel and taste of home.  My friends and I arrived on a Saturday night, ordered the awesome fries, the sticky wings, mac and cheese, and a turkey lamb burger.  The awesome fries were indeed awesome, the sticky wings lived up to the hype, the mac and cheese had the perfect taste of home, and the burger was set over the top by home made pickles.  The prices were reasonable and the service excellent.  The timing of the meal was right, the awesome fries making their way to our table minutes after ordering, and the entree to follow. The entire experience took roughly an hour, but for food made in-house, I'd easily wait that again.
Very good
The food and the customer service is excellent. This was my first time eating here and I will definitely be back! I highly recommend you stop by and break bread here!
The vibe is so smooth! Small but beautiful design creates a nice feel. Neosoul playing in the background. Friendly staff.The food is upscale but comforting. A hidden gem.
This place is so great. Food is fantastic and the atmosphere is so comforting. I had the best carrot cake of my entire life here. Do yourself a favor and give this place a visit.
Great place to eat. Good menu.
Food and atmosphere was incredible. Had the catfish and sticky wings and they were both amazing. Jabril was very attentive and delightful. 10/10 would go again.
Awesome food, service and price. I love the bread pudding.

This hole in the wall place has the best wings in Baltimore. Decent service.  If you are here on an slow night sit at the bar for some fun conversation with the friendly staff. Their daily specials are generally acceptional which I usually spring for those. Burgers and fries are okay but not the best.
The food is very good.

This place is amazing. The entire staff is super friendly. I think I was greeted by everyone working by the time I left. The staff is great, but the food is *stellar*. I've never had better lamb, their "Awesome Fries" are really excellent. Basically pulled pork/chicken nachos but fries instead of chips. Super great. And their burgers taste really great, but the other stuff is so much better. Stick with stuff you won't get at every other restaurant.
ABSOLUTELY LOVE everything about this place... It's a great casual atmosphere, super friendly, wonderful and healthy menu, well priced... Love everything!
My aon loves the wings and I love the fried catfish and greek salad. Desserts are awesome too.
They have really good food. And as a cherry on top, their behavior is as sweet as their desserts.
Mrs.Ellis is the GREATEST me and my wife had a great experience the food was delicious... PLEASE TRY THE STICKY WINGS!!!!
Awesome place and love Ms. Kim
The food is great, but some times the wait can be longer than expected. I just call ahead as I'm in route and order whether I'm picking up or dining in. The Sticky wings are my favorite!
those sticky wings are the truth!
The food is always delicious but the customer service is on another level.  Everyone makes you feel at home and that your business is appreciated.  Simply amazing!!!

My meal was totally delicious....I recommend Breaking Bread to everyone....I had the Creole Shrimp and grits....absolutely slamming....and sticky wings....nothing I have ever tasted....and then the sweet potato bread pudding....to die for....I love this spot....Made my birthday really special....And the owner Carla....what a great spirit.....a wonderful person and I was glad to meet her...she does wonderful work....I appreciate her paying it forward.....God Bless her and her family....she has definitely found a customer in me..Thank you so much....

First of all, I was ready to rate this place 5 star and I haven't even gotten their food! The place is a local family owned restaurant, the bathroom is filled with amenities like free pads and tampons and lotion, hand sanitizer, air freshener. The staff were so friendly, the owners themselves approached us how we're doing. Patrons here were also friendly!  Now for the food. The food was as great as the place itself! My sister and I got Awesome Fries and the sticky wings! Omg it was soooo good! Awesome fries is a pretty big portion.  The sticky finger is sprinkled with cilantro and scallion, the flavor is just right. My sister is a big fan of wings and later told me she's still thinking about those wings!  Overall a great restaurant, food, atmosphere, staff, owners, patrons!

First time visiting "Breaking Bread Restaurant" I must say excellent service thanks to JABRIL & great food. JABRIL was a great help after I discovered my debit card was left at the parking garage; offered to treat me to some wings. I don't even eat sticky wings and from the time I bit into them, OMG finger licking delicious. I will definitely recommend this restaurant to anyone visting and living in the Baltimore area.
The sticky wings are delicious. I will definitely be back. You can tell that the food is made with love.
Known for Sticky wings but everything on the menu is awesome.  Great atmosphere,  friendly service.
This is a true family restaurant. Owned & operated by a family. You'll feel welcomed & right at home. And the food is quite good. Voted the BEST sticky wings in Baltimore!!!!
This place is the best restauraunt ive ever ate at PERIOD!!!!!!
Best burger I have ever had and best food in general. Service is great much hospitality. Would 200% reccomend you go here best food with great service and prices.
Burgers and wings joint that kicks it up several notches, has a real homey atmosphere, and the staff are super friendly.
I love supporting family owned business. The food was delicious.
Great sticky wings. Gotta get some more.
Great conversation with owner and diners and great sticky wings.

The jerk lamb and turkey burger is really, really good, but those awesome fries are my favorite thing on the menu.  How can you go wrong with pulled chicken slathered over some already great tasting fries!  Oh, I almost forgot to mention how good the sweet potato fries are!  Turkey kale and potato soup... delicious!  Great place to sit at the counter and meet new people or sit at the window and people watch.

Great food, great staff! As the sign reads,  "Not fast food, but good food!" Everything is made to order and always,tastes delicious! Every single menu item is tasty, literally! The famous sticky wings will have you licking the bones! Geared toward family and community.

This place is awesome the food is great. I had the soup of the day which was a creamy kale and turkey soup with some potatoes. My main was a jerk lamb and turkey burger it was the best burger I’ve had in years. To top it off the owner is so nice and came to spend time with my party even offered to hold our children while we ate and told us the back story of the restaurant and their charity. 10 our of 10 would go again.
Good food & great staff.  They aim to please and they do just that.  Parking may be little tough but the food will be worth it.

I discovered this gem in September while visiting a friend. The locals didn’t even know about it but I’m an explorer. I had the burgers twice. I ordered the wings for a get together and they were a hit as we’re the fries.  Now that I’m back in the area I can’t wait to order something- maybe another cheeseburger or lamb burger. Staff friendly attentive though can get a bit overwhelmed when busy.

The food was Superb...it was two of us.  We had the Kale, turkey, potato soup (talking gooood and lite).  The turkey burger sweet mother of Turkey burger it was heaven!!!! Cat fish and shrimp with potato salad OMG.  Everything was freshly prepared and clean tasting to the patels.  I REALLLLLY enjoyed All the the food. The dining area has the perfect vibe for Great Food.  Jabril, just made me want to eat more, wonderful personality and I felt like I was at my Grandmother house.  Breaking Bread is a Most Eat dont miss out!  I will be back

2 days in a row I make in and bad a wonderful time. They welcome you with peace and love. This a family affair that is beautiful. The food is F R E S H! SEASONED(no high salt content here!) I started off with the house soup, kale, Turkey sausage &potato...🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥 The catfish was on point... but that turkey burger🤤🤤🤤 make you wanna slap yo momma! But wait the fresh potata salad..... lawwwwddd! And then I had the nerve to have bread pudding.... 👏👏👏👏👏👏👏👏👏😚 If you want to have a soulful experience without the bad attitude and good clean food.... break bread!💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎
My all american burger was perfect!!! Im a new customer for sure

I had some of the most delicious wings EVER here. Chicken is my favorite thing to eat,therefore I am picky about it. I was in town for business and walked in here on a whim,and it was a good idea. I tried the "Stickywings," they were hot, seasoned well,fresh,and DELICIOUS. My only regret about the wings,was that I didn't have more. The catfish and Macaroni were also good. To top it off,my server was delightful,and the Chef came to ask me how I wanted my food,and asked me again if we were still friends later after I ate it,lol,and after those wings,we were friends for life!! It is a quaint little spot,you should go,and you should eat there without a doubt!!!! If i'm in Baltimore again,I wil go back,until I do,go and eat there for me,it's worth it!!!!
Awesome fries are awesome! 😋😋😋
Great food! Absolutely delicious!
It's like eating at your southern grandma's house like LOVE
Love the food here. The owners and staff and great and friendly. Great wings, burger, specials, and breakfast
Service was horrible, took 1 1/2 to get our food. No apologies from the waitstaff. Won't ever go again.
Its ok...
Most food here is delicious but the sticky wings and burgers are indeed my favorite and go to!
Grits were awesome
Wings and burgers are wicked friggin good. Sticky wings are a must, never had better! Fries are perfect. Staff is very friendly. Got kids? No problem!
Fantastic food and friendly, community oriented staff and owners.
Best wings
Pleasant &polite service,great food ,good prices!
GREAT PLACE TO EAT , ALL ARE WELCOME GOOD EVERYTHING !!! ✔✔✔✔✅✅✅✅💯💯💯💯💯💯💯💯💯💯
Food is awesome and staff are super friendly
Great burgers. Very friendly staff. Would highly recommend
The burgers are amazing and the family run vibe is great. The owner is a lovely lady!
Sticky wings is a must try.
The sticky wings are amazing! The menu is great...the atmosphere is laid back and the owner's are real down to earth. If you're looking for a chill spot...this is it.
My first time there a month ago and I fell in love
Friendly's nice atmosphere

Only one single star compared to everyone else's five star...give me a break!!! Went in on a Saturday night with two friends that were in town from Milwaukee. Since it was just the 3 of us we sat at the bar, this was a great idea and I'll come back to that. The food was amazing, just to be blunt. Two burgers were ordered, some sticky wings (get them) and oxtails. My one friend said "i haven't had oxtail this good since my friends grandma back home made it for me" My burger was....lets put it this way when I get great food, i stop talking. I went silent for like 15 minutes so I could enjoy the best burger I've had in 7 years. I ordered it medium well and it was juicy,  flavorful, just perfect. The best part was the owners were there and they are a family. It felt like they welcomed us into their home to dine with them.  To recap: Food "better than your grandma makes" level 5 stars Owners are nice and friendly and I'm so glad they chose Pigtown to open this place in.

I don't know about negative reviews, but I am a Pigtown resident. Two Saturdays ago I walked in looking very tired. A staff member asked me what was wrong and I explained that my mother had a heart attack and I just bought her back from the and I was exhausted.  The chef Kimberly Eliis asked for my address and she and her husband personally delivered my mom a wonderful salmon salad.  My mom was happy and well pleased.  Some things that are done from the heart are better than things that are done for the stomach.  Write that down!  Bernard L. Williams

I agree Mr. Ellis. I have yet to hear of any negative reviews from anyone who has visited this restaurant. I myself am a picky eater who is turned off by the simplest things when it comes to eating out.  Excellent service! Delicious food! Burgers, sticky wings...  You won't be disappointed!!

Breaking Bread is a wonderful little spot in Pigtown.  It opened appropriately on small business Saturday and it has proven itself ever since.  The food is DELICIOUS, the famous sticky wings, the OMG Awesome fries, the everytime delicious potato kale soup, and the forgettaboutit burger with garlic parm fries.  If all that did not make you hungry then go to McDonalds and enjoy the 2:1 menu because you will never appreciate great food!! Must go to place and everyone in the building is as nice as can be!!

While I appreciate the atmosphere and amazing friendly family service, the food is awful and quite bland. Ive been to this place twice and tried to give it a second chance since it had only opened, but i was disappointed again. The Turkey burger has no seasoning and was served luke warm, and the turkey kale soup was pretty luke warm as well. It tasted like milk and kale. No flavor at all! I also think the shredded lettuce served on the burger makes it look sloppy and not worth the$10/$11 I paid for when I could go to Abbey's for an amazing burger at the same price. I had the awesome fries which werent so awesome. The fries were soggy, the bbq pulled beef non existent and dry, and then cheese was poured over everything into one giant mess that really just made it all one glob. Lastly, the cupcakes are HORRENDOUS. If you like your hand to be covered in grease/butter, then I guess this is right up your alley but I was disappointed how heavy and greasy the cupcakes were despite how much the owner raved about it. Its weird they have so many "healthy" options but its all flavorless, and if I'm getting a Turkey Burger with a side salad, I would expect more than just a handful of mesculin greens without any cucumbers or tomatoes or onions for example.  The establishment has potential but they really need to taste their food, season it more, and make sure its HOT. The only consistent thing about this place is that the food is bad. Maybe their salvation is the wings, but I never tried it. I doubt Ill ever go back; at least not anytime soon. They definitely need to work out the kinks.
Good/Delicious Burgers and their Sticky Wings are awesome. We enjoyed our meals and the chef personally came out to welcome us and make sure everything was ok.. 😊  #WINNING
